:15:21 GMT") (guid nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2013/apr/21/egypt-justice-minister-resigns-judiciary") (dc:creator nil "Patrick Kingsley") (dc:subject nil "World news") (dc:date nil "2013-04-21T17:15:21Z") (dc:type nil "Article") (dc:identifier nil "407600404") (media:keywords nil "Egypt, Muslim Brotherhood, Mohamed Morsi, Middle East and North Africa, Africa, World news") (media:content ((height . "84") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "140") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/About/General/2013/4/21/1366564478787/Ahmed-Mekky-003.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Amr Abdallah Dalsh/Reuters") (media:description nil "Ahmed Mekky, pictured last year, resigned over proposewd changes to Egypt's judiciary. Photograph: Amr Abdallah Dalsh/Reuters")) (media:content ((height . "276") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "460") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/About/General/2013/4/21/1366564486217/Ahmed-Mekky-008.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Amr Abdallah Dalsh/Reuters") (media:description nil "Ahmed Mekky, pictured last year, resigned over proposewd changes to Egypt's judiciary. Photograph: Amr Abdallah Dalsh/Reuters")))) ("Guantánamo hunger strikers make up half of inmate population, officials say" "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/96823?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Aguantanamo-bay-hunger-strike-half-inmates%3A1897074&ch=World+news&c3=GU.co.uk&c4=Guantanamo+Bay+%28News%29%2CUS+military+%28News%29%2CUS+news%2CShaker+Aamer%2CWorld+news%2CCuba+%28News%29&c5=Unclassified%2CNot+commercially+useful&c6=Matt+Williams&c7=2013%2F04%2F21+06%3A13&c8=1897074&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Guant%C3%A1namo+hunger+strikers+make+up+half+of+inmate+population%2C+officials+say&c66=News&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FNews%2FWorld+news%2FGuant%C3%A1namo+Bay\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">Eighty-four of the 166 remaining detainees are on hunger strike, a figure almost double the number previously released</p><p>More than half of the remaining detainees at Guantánamo Bay are now on a hunger strike, US military officials confirmed Sunday.</p><p>Of the 166 inmates at the controversial detention camp in Cuba, 84 are refusing all food as a protest against their indefinite confinement and conditions at the centre.</p><p>The figure is almost double the number previously released by officials, although inmates and their lawyers have long suggested that a majority of inmates were taking part.</p><p>Amongst those refusing food is Shaker Aamer, who has spent 11 years at Guantánamo. He remains behind bars <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2013/apr/20/british-resident-guantanamo\">despite being cleared for release six years ago</a>.</p><p>He told the Observer – the Guardian's sister paper – on Sunday that he had lost a quarter of his body weight since going on hunger strike more than 60 days ago.</p><p>\"I barely notice all of my medical ailments any more – the back pain from the beatings I have taken, the rheumatism from the frigid air conditioning, the asthma exacerbated by the toxic sprays they use to abuse us. There is an endless list. And now 24/7, as the Americans say, I have the ache of hunger,\" Aamer said.</p><p>He added: \"I hope I do not die in this awful place. I want to hug my children and watch them as they grow. But if it is God's will that I should die here, I want to die with dignity. I hope, if the worst comes to the worst, that my children will understand that I cared for the rights of those suffering around me almost as much as I care for them.\"</p><p>Of the 84 prisoners on hunger strike, 16 are being force-fed. The military has said that none have life-threatening conditions, but a number of inmates and their lawyers have suggested that some men are close to death as a result of the action.</p><p>Last weekend, guards attempted to break hunger strikers' resolve by forcibly removing them from communal areas and placing them in solitary cells. The move led to violent clashes, with guards firing \"non-lethal\" rounds on prisoners.</p><p>\"The military responds with violence, as if that will break us; it draws us together,\" Aamer told the Observer.</p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/guantanamo-bay\">Guantánamo Bay</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/us-military\">US military</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/usa\">United States</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/shaker-aamer\">Shaker Aamer</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/cuba\">Cuba</a></li></ul></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/matt-williams\">Matt Williams</a></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" />" "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2013/apr/21/guantanamo-bay-hunger-strike-half-inmates" (20852 7708) old 22 nil nil ((title nil "Guantánamo hunger strikers make up half of inmate population, officials say") (link nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2013/apr/21/guantanamo-bay-hunger-strike-half-inmates") (description nil "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/96823?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Aguantanamo-bay-hunger-strike-half-inmates%3A1897074&ch=World+news&c3=GU.co.uk&c4=Guantanamo+Bay+%28News%29%2CUS+military+%28News%29%2CUS+news%2CShaker+Aamer%2CWorld+news%2CCuba+%28News%29&c5=Unclassified%2CNot+commercially+useful&c6=Matt+Williams&c7=2013%2F04%2F21+06%3A13&c8=1897074&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Guant%C3%A1namo+hunger+strikers+make+up+half+of+inmate+population%2C+officials+say&c66=News&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FNews%2FWorld+news%2FGuant%C3%A1namo+Bay\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">Eighty-four of the 166 remaining detainees are on hunger strike, a figure almost double the number previously released</p><p>More than half of the remaining detainees at Guantánamo Bay are now on a hunger strike, US military officials confirmed Sunday.</p><p>Of the 166 inmates at the controversial detention camp in Cuba, 84 are refusing all food as a protest against their indefinite confinement and conditions at the centre.</p><p>The figure is almost double the number previously released by officials, although inmates and their lawyers have long suggested that a majority of inmates were taking part.</p><p>Amongst those refusing food is Shaker Aamer, who has spent 11 years at Guantánamo. He remains behind bars <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2013/apr/20/british-resident-guantanamo\">despite being cleared for release six years ago</a>.</p><p>He told the Observer – the Guardian's sister paper – on Sunday that he had lost a quarter of his body weight since going on hunger strike more than 60 days ago.</p><p>\"I barely notice all of my medical ailments any more – the back pain from the beatings I have taken, the rheumatism from the frigid air conditioning, the asthma exacerbated by the toxic sprays they use to abuse us. There is an endless list. And now 24/7, as the Americans say, I have the ache of hunger,\" Aamer said.</p><p>He added: \"I hope I do not die in this awful place. I want to hug my children and watch them as they grow. But if it is God's will that I should die here, I want to die with dignity. I hope, if the worst comes to the worst, that my children will understand that I cared for the rights of those suffering around me almost as much as I care for them.\"</p><p>Of the 84 prisoners on hunger strike, 16 are being force-fed. The military has said that none have life-threatening conditions, but a number of inmates and their lawyers have suggested that some men are close to death as a result of the action.</p><p>Last weekend, guards attempted to break hunger strikers' resolve by forcibly removing them from communal areas and placing them in solitary cells. The move led to violent clashes, with guards firing \"non-lethal\" rounds on prisoners.</p><p>\"The military responds with violence, as if that will break us; it draws us together,\" Aamer told the Observer.</p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/guantanamo-bay\">Guantánamo Bay</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/us-military\">US military</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/usa\">United States</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/shaker-aamer\">Shaker Aamer</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/cuba\">Cuba</a></li></ul></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/matt-williams\">Matt Williams</a></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" />") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world")) "Guantánamo Bay") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world")) "US military") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world")) "United States") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world")) "Shaker Aamer") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world")) "World news") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world")) "Cuba") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/publication")) "guardian.co.uk") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/tone")) "News") (pubDate nil "Sun, 21 Apr 2013 17:13:00 GMT") (guid nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2013/apr/21/guantanamo-bay-hunger-strike-half-inmates") (dc:creator nil "Matt Williams") (dc:subject nil "World news") (dc:date nil "2013-04-21T17:27:11Z") (dc:type nil "Article") (dc:identifier nil "407599935") (media:keywords nil "Guantánamo Bay, US military, United States, Shaker Aamer, World news, Cuba") (media:content ((height . "84") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "140") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/4/15/1366047178098/Guant-namo-Bay-003.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Bob Strong/Reuters") (media:description nil "Guards swept through communal cellblocks at Guantánamo and moved the prisoners into one-man cells in an attempt to end a hunger strike. Photograph: Bob Strong/Reuters")) (media:content ((height . "276") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "460") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/4/15/1366047186892/Guant-namo-Bay-008.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Bob Strong/Reuters") (media:description nil "Guards moved Guantánamo prisoners into one-man cells in an attempt to end the strike. Photograph: Bob Strong/Reuters")))) ("North Korea moves more missile launchers to east coast, says report" "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/88632?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Anorth-korea-missile-launchers-east-coast%3A1897068&ch=World+news&c3=Guardian&c4=North+Korea+%28News%29%2CSouth+Korea+%28News%29%2CAsia+Pacific+%28News%29%2CWorld+news&c5=Unclassified%2CNot+commercially+useful%2CMotorsport&c6=Reuters+in+Seoul&c7=2013%2F04%2F21+05%3A53&c8=1897068&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=North+Korea+moves+more+missile+launchers+to+east+coast%2C+says+report&c66=News&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FNews%2FWorld+news%2FNorth+Korea\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">South Korean military source tells news agency satellite images shows move, suggesting preparations for test launch</p><p>North Korea has moved two short-range missile launchers to its east coast , apparently indicating it is going ahead with preparations for a test launch, a South Korean news agency reported.</p><p>Seoul and its allies have been expecting some sort of missile launch during weeks of heightened hostility on the Korean peninsula.</p><p>An unidentified South Korean military source told the Yonhap news agency that satellite imagery showed two mobile launchers for short-range Scud missiles had been moved to South Hamgyeong province. \"The military is closely watching the North's latest preparations for a missile launch,\" the source said.</p><p>The North moved two mid-range Musudan missiles in early April and placed seven mobile launchers in the same area, Yonhap said on Sunday. A North Korean show of force could be staged to coincide with the anniversary of the founding of its army on 25 April.</p><p>A South Korean defence ministry official said he could not confirm the news report, adding that there had been no sign of unusual activity in the North. North Korea regularly test-fires short-range missiles in the sea off its east coast.</p><p>Pyongyang stepped up its defiance of UN security council resolutions in December when it launched a rocket it said had delivered a scientific satellite into orbit. Critics said the launch was aimed at developing technology to deliver a nuclear warhead mounted on a long-range missile.</p><p>In February North Korea carried out its third test of a nuclear weapon, triggering new UN sanctions which in turn led to a dramatic intensification of Pyonyang's threats of nuclear strikes against South Korea and the US.</p><p>The tension has eased over recent days with North Korea at least talking about dialogue in response to calls for talks from the US and the South Korea.</p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/north-korea\">North Korea</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/south-korea\">South Korea</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/asia-pacific\">Asia Pacific</a></li></ul></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" />" "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2013/apr/21/north-korea-missile-launchers-east-coast" (20852 6545) old 23 nil nil ((title nil "North Korea moves more missile launchers to east coast, says report") (link nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2013/apr/21/north-korea-missile-launchers-east-coast") (description nil "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/88632?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Anorth-korea-missile-launchers-east-coast%3A1897068&ch=World+news&c3=Guardian&c4=North+Korea+%28News%29%2CSouth+Korea+%28News%29%2CAsia+Pacific+%28News%29%2CWorld+news&c5=Unclassified%2CNot+commercially+useful%2CMotorsport&c6=Reuters+in+Seoul&c7=2013%2F04%2F21+05%3A53&c8=1897068&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=North+Korea+moves+more+missile+launchers+to+east+coast%2C+says+report&c66=News&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FNews%2FWorld+news%2FNorth+Korea\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">South Korean military source tells news agency satellite images shows move, suggesting preparations for test launch</p><p>North Korea has moved two short-range missile launchers to i